==English==
===Alternative spellings===
*sometimes hyphenated or expressed as a phrase: '''pan-deistical''', '''pan deistical'''
*sometimes either the P or both the P and the initial T are capitalized: '''Pandeistical''', '''PanDeistical'''
*variations of capitalization and spacing may be combined: '''Pan-deistical''', '''Pan-Deistical''', '''Pan Deistical''', '''Pan deistical'''
===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} ''[[πάν]]'' (pán) "all"
and {{L.}} ''[[deus]]'' "god"

